Vera Maresova, 50, confessed to killing five women and one man over a four-year period at a hospital in Rumburk - a small town in the Czech Republic .
She injected the potassium straight into the blood stream of her patients, which caused them to suffer heart failure and eventually death .
Maresova was initially arrested over the death of a 70-year-old woman last August but has now admitted killing five more .